cs.DS, cs.IR, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.CE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper introduces a new data structure called the packed compact trie and discusses its performance in terms of space and time complexity. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as the paper mentions pattern matching queries and updates, which are common tasks in information retrieval. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is another possibility as the paper involves combinatorial and graph-theoretic concepts such as tries and suffix trees. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a potential category as the paper discusses worst-case and expected time complexity of the proposed data structure. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses practical applications of the proposed data structure in online LZD factorization and sparse suffix tree construction.
